50
00:03:40.765 --> 00:03:43.901
Oh, hi, Helena.
See you at football later.


51
00:03:44.836 --> 00:03:46.403
Yeah. See you.

52
00:03:56.014 --> 00:03:57.682
Lowy, the Jew.

53
00:03:58.382 --> 00:04:00.183
[Emil] <i>Refuel Lowy was the head</i>

54
00:04:00.317 --> 00:04:02.920
<i>of the Jewish community</i>
<i>in Bardejov.</i>


55
00:04:03.054 --> 00:04:05.155
<i>He was a successful businessman</i>

56
00:04:05.288 --> 00:04:06.824
<i>and a winemaker.</i>

57
00:04:06.958 --> 00:04:09.894
<i>Those who knew him,</i>
<i>respected him.</i>


58
00:04:10.028 --> 00:04:12.497
<i>And those who didn't,</i>
<i>feared him.</i>


59
00:04:13.698 --> 00:04:16.233
You couldn't wait
'til a decent hour?


60
00:04:21.606 --> 00:04:22.907
Yes,

61
00:04:23.041 --> 00:04:26.276
[indistinct] into
the General Council at night.


62
00:04:28.446 --> 00:04:30.280
You'll be hearing from us.

63
00:04:33.151 --> 00:04:35.252
Oh, please,

64
00:04:35.385 --> 00:04:37.855
and pay your drivers
better next time.


65
00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:44.562
Maybe it's not a good time...

66
00:04:45.262 --> 00:04:47.832
to bark orders, Mr. Lowy.

67
00:04:48.398 --> 00:04:49.667
[Stefan clicks tongue]

68
00:04:50.435 --> 00:04:51.703
[Lowy clicks tongue]

69
