106
00:07:50.014 --> 00:07:52.550
Mama, we'll be back soon.
I'm going with Helena.


107
00:07:54.585 --> 00:07:56.087
[guard speaking
other language]


108
00:07:57.054 --> 00:07:58.122
Shh.

109
00:08:04.528 --> 00:08:06.564
-What is this?
-Shh.


110
00:08:16.540 --> 00:08:20.077
[guards speaking
other language]


111
00:08:23.447 --> 00:08:25.583
My parents say this is for real.

112
00:08:31.088 --> 00:08:34.025
I heard they've made
a deal with the Germans.


113
00:08:34.158 --> 00:08:35.459
Of course they have.

114
00:08:35.593 --> 00:08:37.662
That's why the Germans
leaves us alone.


115
00:08:39.931 --> 00:08:41.866
I just picked this with mom.

116
00:08:43.401 --> 00:08:44.802
Thank you, Magda.

117
00:08:44.936 --> 00:08:46.270
-Thank you.
-Take this.


118
00:08:46.404 --> 00:08:48.572
[indistinct whispering]

119
00:08:51.342 --> 00:08:54.578
[speaking other language]

120
00:08:55.680 --> 00:08:57.048
[all] Amen.

121
00:09:10.328 --> 00:09:12.196
My father says we're exempt.

122
00:09:12.330 --> 00:09:13.531
They need us all to work

123
00:09:13.664 --> 00:09:15.666
that's why
they closed the schools.


124
00:09:16.634 --> 00:09:18.269
I'd rather work
than go to school.


125
00:09:18.402 --> 00:09:19.670
[Giselle chuckles]

126
00:09:19.804 --> 00:09:23.607
My-- my father
wants us to leave...


127
00:09:24.308 --> 00:09:25.576
for Hungary.

128
00:09:26.577 --> 00:09:28.579
He says this is a big sign.

129
00:09:29.947 --> 00:09:31.916
My cousins
from Poland just came.


130
00:09:33.250 --> 00:09:35.720
They say they'll be rounding up
[indistinct] and shooting--


131
00:09:35.853 --> 00:09:38.055
Shh. [speaking other language]

132
00:09:38.189 --> 00:09:39.323
Don't talk like that.

133
00:09:39.458 --> 00:09:41.125
All the rumors are to scare us.

134
00:09:42.326 --> 00:09:45.563
Let's meet here
every morning eight o'clock.


135
00:09:45.963 --> 00:09:47.698
Bring whatever news you have.

136
00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:51.268
I'll have one other
[indistinct] to borrow


137
00:09:51.402 --> 00:09:52.636
from goyish families.

138
00:09:53.137 --> 00:09:56.640
Make sure every family
have a [indistinct], okay?


139
00:09:56.774 --> 00:09:58.743
-All right.
-All right. Magda.


140
00:09:58.876 --> 00:10:00.479
Magda, you bring the cake.

141
00:10:00.611 --> 00:10:01.946
Yes.

142
00:10:02.380 --> 00:10:03.614
We are strong.

143
00:10:04.548 --> 00:10:06.751
-We are fighters.
-[indistinct]


144
00:10:06.884 --> 00:10:09.020
We're together. 
We'll be okay.

145
00:10:09.454 --> 00:10:12.590
[whistles] Take us to
the headquarters, [indistinct].


146
00:10:13.124 --> 00:10:16.193
Hey, I'm not getting back
what that Jew said.


147
00:10:16.327 --> 00:10:17.294
Slow down.

148
00:10:17.429 --> 00:10:21.298
[overlapping chatter]

149
00:10:24.668 --> 00:10:26.871
-Oh! What the--
-Jesus!


150
00:10:28.606 --> 00:10:31.275
Perfect timing.
Give Bomba the mail.


151
00:10:31.776 --> 00:10:33.277
Okay. Yes.

152
00:10:34.513 --> 00:10:36.814
To General Kovac in Bratislava.

153
00:10:36.947 --> 00:10:38.983
Right away, Captain.

154
00:10:39.884 --> 00:10:43.954
[Emil] <i>General Kovac was</i>
<i>the captain of the Hlinka Guard</i>


155
00:10:44.088 --> 00:10:47.024
<i>overseeing</i>
<i>the Bardejov district.</i>


156
00:10:47.792 --> 00:10:49.760
<i>He was a snake in the grass</i>

157
00:10:49.894 --> 00:10:52.563
<i>and Stefan's main superior.</i>

158
00:11:04.708 --> 00:11:08.245
[singing in other language]

159
00:11:32.504 --> 00:11:34.105
From Adam.

160
00:11:47.351 --> 00:11:48.686
What does it say?

161
00:11:57.394 --> 00:11:58.963
Give this back to him.

162
00:12:02.299 --> 00:12:03.701
With this.

163
00:12:03.834 --> 00:12:05.102
All right.

164
00:12:05.470 --> 00:12:06.538
He is a good man.

165
00:12:07.037 --> 00:12:08.873
Passion should keep him safe.

166
00:12:10.007 --> 00:12:12.209
-We need him.
-I will see you upstairs.


167
00:12:12.343 --> 00:12:14.078
-I'll bring the [indistinct].
-Yes.


168
00:12:14.211 --> 00:12:16.914
And the others, we need
the whole Jewish Council.


169
00:12:17.549 --> 00:12:19.417
And-- and coffee.

170
00:12:20.117 --> 00:12:22.386
Please tell my son,
[indistinct], to fetch me one.


171
00:12:22.521 --> 00:12:23.854
I haven't slept.

172
00:12:34.798 --> 00:12:36.066
Thank you, Ben.

173
00:12:43.741 --> 00:12:45.242
Halberstam,
with your permission.


174
00:12:45.376 --> 00:12:47.044
-Sure.
-Sure.


175
00:12:49.713 --> 00:12:51.782
Clearly I couldn't
stop the order.


176
00:12:53.050 --> 00:12:56.153
Now we handed a letter
to give to President Tiso


177
00:12:56.287 --> 00:12:59.256
requesting assurance
that the work will stay local


178
00:12:59.390 --> 00:13:02.026
and that, uh,
protect the Slovakian Jews


179
00:13:02.159 --> 00:13:03.894
from German deportations.

180
00:13:04.695 --> 00:13:06.964
-Assurance?
-What kind of assurance?


181
00:13:07.097 --> 00:13:09.534
Clearly we don't believe
their promises, all right?


182
00:13:09.668 --> 00:13:12.002
They're trying to make good
for the independence


183
00:13:12.136 --> 00:13:14.639
and they have to give
Hitler what he-- what he wants.


184
00:13:14.772 --> 00:13:15.806
They need us.

185
00:13:16.441 --> 00:13:18.175
The sheer numbers
of the economic force


186
00:13:18.309 --> 00:13:20.545
of the Slovakian Jews is
something to show the Germans.


187
00:13:20.945 --> 00:13:23.013
-Foolish to deport us.
-[Mayer] Absolutely.


188
00:13:23.147 --> 00:13:25.483
Yeah, but we also
received a telegram from, uh,


189
00:13:25.617 --> 00:13:28.420
the German other secretary,
uh, Martin, uh--


190
00:13:28.553 --> 00:13:30.154
-Martin Luther?
-Yes.


191
00:13:30.287 --> 00:13:33.257
They're requesting

192
00:13:33.390 --> 00:13:35.326
to work in the East.

193
00:13:36.860 --> 00:13:38.762
Now they're registering us.

194
00:13:39.730 --> 00:13:42.066
-That's just the beginning.
-It's just for show.


195
00:13:42.199 --> 00:13:46.504
20,000, 90,000
Jews in all of Slovakia.


196
00:13:46.638 --> 00:13:49.106
And Tiso is going to pay...

197
00:13:50.140 --> 00:13:52.943
20,000 German marks per Jew

198
00:13:53.077 --> 00:13:55.045
to Hitler for the privilege.

199
00:13:55.179 --> 00:13:58.182
Ah, so we are making the money

200
00:13:58.315 --> 00:14:01.185
to pay for our own deportation.

201
00:14:02.119 --> 00:14:04.623
What's the plan?
Who's getting deported?


202
00:14:04.755 --> 00:14:06.190
Those who can walk, I suppose.

203
00:14:06.323 --> 00:14:09.260
I don't think
they have a plan right now.


204
00:14:09.994 --> 00:14:12.129
But it's important that we keep

205
00:14:12.263 --> 00:14:15.165
playing the game
for the time being.


206
00:14:15.299 --> 00:14:18.335
But it's important
to put a message out there.


207
00:14:18.470 --> 00:14:20.037
People need to register.

208
00:14:20.170 --> 00:14:23.007
We have to go through
these motions here.


209
00:14:23.140 --> 00:14:26.110
There are 450 families
in Bardejov.


210
00:14:27.545 --> 00:14:30.080
4600 people.

211
00:14:30.214 --> 00:14:31.650
Listen,

212
00:14:31.782 --> 00:14:33.951
purim is [indistinct] Shaboss.

213
00:14:34.084 --> 00:14:36.421
All right, let's keep
things normal, Rabbi.


214
00:14:36.554 --> 00:14:40.492
We need to make everything
just like <i>pur.</i>


215
00:14:41.292 --> 00:14:43.927
Turn it on its head,
God willing.


216
00:14:44.061 --> 00:14:45.329
[Rabbi speaking
other language]


217
00:14:45.929 --> 00:14:47.097
Amen.

218
00:14:47.231 --> 00:14:48.700
[Rabbi speaking
other language]


219
00:14:48.832 --> 00:14:51.302
Thursday is Taanit Esther.

220
00:14:52.403 --> 00:14:54.706
Two and a half
thousand years ago,


221
00:14:54.838 --> 00:14:56.807
she demanded a fast.

222
00:14:56.940 --> 00:14:59.678
We listened and we were saved.

223
00:15:00.377 --> 00:15:04.582
Make sure everyone
is fasting this time as well.


224
00:15:04.716 --> 00:15:06.317
It's-- it's important.

225
00:15:07.351 --> 00:15:09.587
Also, please...

226
00:15:10.455 --> 00:15:13.324
make sure that you have
a plan for your families.


227
00:15:13.924 --> 00:15:15.326
You understand?

228
00:15:16.461 --> 00:15:20.230
What about all the Polish Jews
that have come flooding in?


229
00:15:20.364 --> 00:15:22.232
Yeah, that's a--
that's a good point.


230
00:15:22.366 --> 00:15:23.967
Mayer,

231
00:15:24.101 --> 00:15:26.236
try to tell Helena
to stop for right now.


232
00:15:26.370 --> 00:15:28.372
All right?
Your daughter will understand.


233
00:15:30.407 --> 00:15:33.277
I-- I-- I don't know
how we can do anything.


234
00:15:33.410 --> 00:15:34.978
Well, she's a very
clever girl, all right?


235
00:15:35.112 --> 00:15:37.114
She's arranged
for hundreds of them.


236
00:15:37.981 --> 00:15:39.451
She can figure out a way.

237
00:15:40.217 --> 00:15:43.120
It makes sense to think
Slovakia is different.


238
00:15:43.253 --> 00:15:46.624
Safer, but we cannot
take the risk anymore.


239
00:15:46.758 --> 00:15:49.226
[Mayer] What risk is it
to us to help them?


240
00:15:49.360 --> 00:15:52.464
[Lowy] How about overcrowding,
rations, typhus.


241
00:15:52.597 --> 00:15:54.298
Our leverage
is in our workforce.


242
00:15:54.432 --> 00:15:56.934
We need to remain
healthy, productive.


243
00:15:57.067 --> 00:15:58.436
This will protect us.

244
00:15:58.570 --> 00:16:00.772
[Mayer] We cannot
turn Jews away.


245
00:16:00.904 --> 00:16:02.440
[Lowy] I understand that,

246
00:16:02.574 --> 00:16:06.043
but we have to comply
with the order to buy more time.


247
00:16:06.578 --> 00:16:07.779
Curfew at seven.

248
00:16:07.911 --> 00:16:09.748
No doing business with Aryans.

249
00:16:10.114 --> 00:16:12.584
No walking on
the same side of the street.


250
00:16:13.016 --> 00:16:16.387
It's important
that we be very smart.


251
00:16:16.855 --> 00:16:18.790
We be close to our families,

252
00:16:18.922 --> 00:16:22.960
close to each other
and make sure that we understand


253
00:16:23.093 --> 00:16:25.864
that we are living
in very dangerous times.


254
00:16:26.431 --> 00:16:29.868
We-- we just
put our trust in God


255
00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:31.902
and pray for the best.

256
00:16:32.035 --> 00:16:34.371
We-- we have to believe...

257
00:16:35.105 --> 00:16:36.474
he will save us.

258
00:16:40.177 --> 00:16:43.782
Friends, it's important
that you register.


259
00:16:44.181 --> 00:16:46.551
Each family head
must register his family.


260
00:16:46.684 --> 00:16:49.454
We have to keep to the codex.
We have to be under the radar.


261
00:16:49.587 --> 00:16:51.989
Do what they ask us
to do so we can...


262
00:16:52.824 --> 00:16:54.191
work things out, please.

263
00:16:54.659 --> 00:16:57.327
It's better
we cooperate and keep calm.


264
00:16:59.062 --> 00:17:00.598
Hashem will keep us safe.

265
00:17:03.701 --> 00:17:06.036
Go upstairs.
Get your toys there.


266
00:17:06.170 --> 00:17:07.572
We'll go eat soon. Okay?

267
00:17:09.306 --> 00:17:10.274
-Hi.
-Hi.


268
00:17:10.407 --> 00:17:11.843
I'm going to lie down.

269
00:17:11.975 --> 00:17:14.111
I know. I know, Refuel.
But two minutes.


270
00:17:14.244 --> 00:17:16.046
[sighs] Roza, please.

271
00:17:16.180 --> 00:17:17.715
I promise we'll <i>schmues</i> later.

272
00:17:17.849 --> 00:17:20.184
I know, I know, but not me.

273
00:17:20.819 --> 00:17:23.153
-I promised them.
-Huh?


274
00:17:26.558 --> 00:17:28.258
[sighs] Really?

275
00:17:28.392 --> 00:17:30.895
They're your uncle's cousins,
your family.


276
00:17:31.028 --> 00:17:32.597
[Lowy groans]

277
00:17:33.531 --> 00:17:35.567
Yes. All Jews are family.

278
00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:37.234
Things are not
better here anymore.


279
00:17:37.367 --> 00:17:38.736
Things are much better here.

280
00:17:38.870 --> 00:17:41.338
Refuel, listen to what
they have to say.


281
00:17:41.906 --> 00:17:43.541
-Only two.
-Only two.


282
00:17:53.685 --> 00:17:56.454
-We have the room.
-We have the room.


283
00:17:57.354 --> 00:17:59.156
We have nothing but room.

284
00:18:00.458 --> 00:18:03.561
[laughs] Okay. All right.

285
00:18:10.502 --> 00:18:13.036
-[indistinct].
-They have our address, Helena.


286
00:18:13.170 --> 00:18:15.105
Did you plaster our address

287
00:18:15.239 --> 00:18:17.241
on every ghetto in Poland?

288
00:18:17.374 --> 00:18:20.110
Helena, we need
to stop them coming.


289
00:18:20.244 --> 00:18:23.113
-It's not helping--
-I cannot, Daddy.


290
00:18:24.281 --> 00:18:25.884
We have a good system.

291
00:18:26.016 --> 00:18:27.284
We're better off than they are.

292
00:18:27.418 --> 00:18:29.186
They know that.
And you know that.


293
00:18:29.319 --> 00:18:33.190
Mr. Lowy says
that we're already too crowded


294
00:18:33.323 --> 00:18:35.225
and they bring typhus.

295
00:18:35.359 --> 00:18:36.661
Let's see him turn them away.

296
00:18:37.929 --> 00:18:40.130
Darling, I'm not sure Bardejov

297
00:18:40.264 --> 00:18:42.934
is as protected
as they think it is.


298
00:18:43.066 --> 00:18:45.335
As you think it is.

299
00:18:46.069 --> 00:18:49.807
[Emil] <i>Jewish businesses</i>
<i>were handed over to non-Jews.</i>


300
00:18:49.941 --> 00:18:51.976
<i>They were known as</i> [indistinct]

301
00:18:52.109 --> 00:18:55.647
<i>put in place to control</i>
<i>the Jewish businesses.</i>


302
00:18:55.780 --> 00:18:58.416
<i>Fredrik</i>
<i>was Lowy's</i> [indistinct],


303
00:18:58.550 --> 00:19:00.919
<i>but also his friend.</i>

304
00:19:01.419 --> 00:19:03.253
You should have signed them,
Herr Director.


305
00:19:03.387 --> 00:19:05.023
You are the boss now, Fredrik.

306
00:19:05.155 --> 00:19:06.558
It seems absurd.

307
00:19:07.025 --> 00:19:08.526
Yeah, it is.

308
00:19:08.660 --> 00:19:11.429
Herr Director, you and your
family are sorted, yeah?


309
00:19:13.297 --> 00:19:15.098
I can't do anything
for any of these people.


310
00:19:15.232 --> 00:19:17.301
But for you
and Roza and the boys.


311
00:19:17.435 --> 00:19:19.269
We are good.
It's very kind, Fredrik.


312
00:19:19.403 --> 00:19:21.573
I-- We have the--
the yellow card.


313
00:19:21.706 --> 00:19:24.341
All right,
so we exempt at least--


314
00:19:24.475 --> 00:19:26.010
at least from this one.

315
00:19:26.844 --> 00:19:29.814
And Lowy,
you know if you ever need...


316
00:19:30.715 --> 00:19:32.850
I have a place for you
just outside these walls.


317
00:19:32.984 --> 00:19:34.485
It's my father's place.

318
00:19:35.787 --> 00:19:37.855
They've asked us
to take your passports.


319
00:19:37.989 --> 00:19:39.524
[sighs] Yes.

320
00:19:40.525 --> 00:19:43.661
First, all rights then property.

321
00:19:43.795 --> 00:19:45.964
[laughs] And now papers.

322
00:19:46.129 --> 00:19:48.265
Well, we're losing us to dogs.

323
00:19:48.398 --> 00:19:50.635
It's still better
than having the Germans here.


324
00:19:50.768 --> 00:19:53.671
Well, it's only because
you all so incompetent.


325
00:19:53.805 --> 00:19:55.105
[Lowy laughs]

326
00:19:55.573 --> 00:19:58.175
Besides, we have, uh,
bigger jobs to do right now.


327
00:19:58.308 --> 00:19:59.944
Purim.

328
00:20:00.377 --> 00:20:03.146
There we go, you know, Fredrik,
you could pass as a Jew.


329
00:20:03.280 --> 00:20:06.084
Yes, purim.
Not tomorrow. The next day.


330
00:20:06.884 --> 00:20:09.954
And everyone is getting
whatever wine they want


331
00:20:10.088 --> 00:20:11.355
for whatever they can give.

332
00:20:11.489 --> 00:20:12.957
And this is an order.
You understand?


333
00:20:13.091 --> 00:20:14.525
You're asking me to take a loss.

334
00:20:14.659 --> 00:20:16.594
Well, don't worry.
You'll make it up somehow.


335
00:20:17.528 --> 00:20:19.998
I want to thank you
for recruiting Adam.


336
00:20:20.431 --> 00:20:22.600
He brought us
some very important information


337
00:20:22.734 --> 00:20:23.801
this morning.

338
00:20:26.638 --> 00:20:29.474
This is a sanctuary
more than a factory.


339
00:20:29.607 --> 00:20:31.141
Mm.

340
00:20:31.943 --> 00:20:33.811
Make sure today and tomorrow

341
00:20:33.945 --> 00:20:37.280
everyone has a chance to go
to the main square and register.


342
00:20:37.415 --> 00:20:38.950
-Yes.
-Stagger the groups.


343
00:20:39.083 --> 00:20:40.350
Okay? Keep them busy.

344
00:20:40.485 --> 00:20:42.587
Yes. Yes. I-
- I saw the notice.

345
00:20:45.723 --> 00:20:47.725
I wish this was
just a formality.


346
00:20:53.598 --> 00:20:56.266
<i>-Na Zdravie!</i>
-[all] <i>Na Zdravie!</i>


347
00:20:57.502 --> 00:20:59.637
<i>Na Zdravie.</i>
Let's see the papers.


348
00:20:59.771 --> 00:21:00.838
Oh.

349
00:21:04.207 --> 00:21:07.011
We don't know what they want
from all those Jews here.


350
00:21:07.145 --> 00:21:10.014
Work, they're following orders
like good little Jews.


351
00:21:10.148 --> 00:21:13.151
They already work for us.
We own all their bloody stores.


352
00:21:13.283 --> 00:21:14.485
[Pieter]
I hear Tiso asked Himmler


353
00:21:14.619 --> 00:21:15.987
to take the whole lot of them.

354
00:21:16.120 --> 00:21:17.755
All 90,000 Jews in Slovakia.

355
00:21:17.889 --> 00:21:19.457
[Slav]
Himmler wanted the Jews out.


356
00:21:20.024 --> 00:21:22.894
Tiso asked him
to have them never return.


357
00:21:24.529 --> 00:21:25.763
You know what that means?

358
00:21:25.897 --> 00:21:27.197
That's why
they registering them.


359
00:21:27.330 --> 00:21:28.900
We are paying the Germans?

360
00:21:30.668 --> 00:21:31.936
20,000.

361
00:21:33.303 --> 00:21:36.040
-20,000 what?
-20,000.


362
00:21:36.541 --> 00:21:39.010
The order is for 20,000.

363
00:21:39.143 --> 00:21:41.344
20,000 for what?

364
00:21:41.879 --> 00:21:43.481
Jews, you idiot.

365
00:21:43.614 --> 00:21:46.316
Signed by Martin Luther himself.

366
00:21:46.818 --> 00:21:48.820
But we don't have
more than 4,000 here.


367
00:21:48.953 --> 00:21:49.987
Yeah.

368
00:21:50.121 --> 00:21:52.790
Not all of them, you moron.

369
00:21:52.924 --> 00:21:54.492
20,000 total.

370
00:21:54.625 --> 00:21:56.060
-For what?
-For work.


371
00:21:56.194 --> 00:21:57.260
You mean for death?

372
00:21:58.029 --> 00:22:01.298
What the German do with Jews,
it's not our problem.


373
00:22:02.232 --> 00:22:03.968
Our problem is Kovac

374
00:22:04.102 --> 00:22:07.404
and these bastards
who treat us like dogs.


375
00:22:09.339 --> 00:22:11.274
Their power
is going to their heads.


376
00:22:16.180 --> 00:22:19.249
Bratislava. Bratislava.

377
00:22:19.382 --> 00:22:22.252
-[guard groans, spits]
-[all laugh]


378
00:22:23.154 --> 00:22:24.989
They're sending replacements.

379
00:22:26.557 --> 00:22:28.126
-Jews?
-Guards.


380
00:22:28.893 --> 00:22:30.928
We are not to do nothing
until they come.


381
00:22:31.062 --> 00:22:33.431
My brother
in [indistinct] in Kosice,


382
00:22:33.564 --> 00:22:34.866
he told me that
they're all [indistinct].


383
00:22:34.999 --> 00:22:37.135
-So they switch them up.
-But not us.


384
00:22:37.267 --> 00:22:38.301
No.

385
00:22:38.436 --> 00:22:40.403
We can do the job ourselves.

386
00:22:42.073 --> 00:22:45.543
We call a curfew tomorrow
for all the Jews.


387
00:22:45.676 --> 00:22:47.377
Is that what it says?

388
00:22:50.481 --> 00:22:51.749
That what I said.

389
00:22:52.483 --> 00:22:55.753
[singing in other language]

390
00:23:21.279 --> 00:23:24.782
[clamoring]

391
00:23:24.916 --> 00:23:27.051
[indistinct].

392
00:23:27.185 --> 00:23:28.553
[all cheering]

393
00:23:28.686 --> 00:23:30.721
I want 100 at least.

394
00:23:30.855 --> 00:23:33.090
-[all laugh]
-To the brewery.


395
00:23:33.724 --> 00:23:35.226
We're waiting for [indistinct].

396
00:23:35.358 --> 00:23:37.595
[all shouting]

397
00:23:39.463 --> 00:23:41.766
[Helena] What is this? Hey!

398
00:23:42.332 --> 00:23:44.168
Wait! No! No!

399
00:23:44.302 --> 00:23:45.837
-[indistinct], Daddy!
-No!


400
00:23:45.970 --> 00:23:46.938
Daddy, no!

401
00:23:47.071 --> 00:23:48.371
Let him go. Let him go.

402
00:23:48.506 --> 00:23:51.976
-Let him--
-My baby! My baby!


403
00:23:52.375 --> 00:23:54.377
[guards speaking
other language]


404
00:23:54.512 --> 00:23:56.346
Please. Please.
[indistinct], please, please.


405
00:23:56.480 --> 00:23:59.183
[overlapping shouting]

406
00:23:59.317 --> 00:24:00.985
[indistinct]

407
00:24:01.118 --> 00:24:03.487
[clamoring]

408
00:24:05.756 --> 00:24:09.293
-Where's my kid? Jozef!
-Get down!


409
00:24:09.794 --> 00:24:11.128
[indistinct], wake up!

410
00:24:13.097 --> 00:24:14.232
Magda, [indistinct].

411
00:24:14.364 --> 00:24:15.733
Come on, wake up.

412
00:24:18.302 --> 00:24:19.402
Wake up.

413
00:24:19.537 --> 00:24:22.807
Mr. Lowy! Open up, please.

414
00:24:23.241 --> 00:24:25.843
They took our kid. Mr. Lowy!

415
00:24:26.477 --> 00:24:28.079
[clamoring]

416
00:24:31.916 --> 00:24:34.719
Stefan, you sure
you have a plan?


417
00:24:34.852 --> 00:24:37.255
-[people sobbing]
-How many now?


418
00:24:37.822 --> 00:24:39.790
-[Slav laughs]
-[people sobbing]


419
00:24:39.924 --> 00:24:41.626
The brewery's almost full.

420
00:24:41.759 --> 00:24:43.995
[sobbing continues]

421
00:24:45.429 --> 00:24:46.564
Good.

422
00:24:47.131 --> 00:24:50.768
See, we know
how to round up Jews.


423
00:24:53.571 --> 00:24:56.040
What the hell are you planning
to do with all the crying?


424
00:24:56.173 --> 00:24:57.842
We not babysitter, Stefan.

425
00:24:58.276 --> 00:24:59.677
Figure it out.

426
00:25:00.478 --> 00:25:02.480
Do whatever you need to do.

427
00:25:04.315 --> 00:25:06.117
[Stefan speaking
other language]


428
00:25:07.785 --> 00:25:10.021
Why you crying? Huh?

429
00:25:12.490 --> 00:25:13.758
Does anyone know
what's going on?


430
00:25:13.891 --> 00:25:14.959
Shh!

431
00:25:18.296 --> 00:25:20.131
What are we going to do here?

432
00:25:25.136 --> 00:25:26.203
Helena.

433
00:25:29.307 --> 00:25:30.775
They're down in the brewery.

434
00:25:31.409 --> 00:25:32.710
Come on, let's go.
Let's help them.


435
00:25:32.843 --> 00:25:34.478
-Are you mad?
-We have to help them.


436
00:25:34.612 --> 00:25:36.147
Helena, Magda [indistinct].

437
00:25:36.614 --> 00:25:37.848
Are you kidding?

438
00:25:37.982 --> 00:25:39.483
I know half
of these Hlinka Guards.


439
00:25:40.184 --> 00:25:41.886
Come on. Come on.

440
00:25:43.721 --> 00:25:46.223
What the hell
is going on, Reisteiter?


441
00:25:47.358 --> 00:25:49.493
Captain.

442
00:25:49.627 --> 00:25:51.896
Captain Reisteiter to you.

443
00:25:53.364 --> 00:25:55.099
I demand to know immediately.

444
00:25:57.868 --> 00:25:59.236
By what authority?

445
00:26:00.237 --> 00:26:03.274
I am the head of
the Jewish Council at Bardejov.


446
00:26:03.407 --> 00:26:05.476
Ah. [laughs]

447
00:26:05.609 --> 00:26:07.678
[guards chuckling]

448
00:26:07.812 --> 00:26:10.748
In that case,
you can sign their work orders.


449
00:26:12.316 --> 00:26:16.087
These are Jewish children
under my jurisdiction.


450
00:26:16.220 --> 00:26:17.355
Your concern.

451
00:26:17.989 --> 00:26:20.157
But not your jurisdiction.

452
00:26:21.559 --> 00:26:24.495
-This is my property.
-It was.


453
00:26:25.296 --> 00:26:28.366
But it's been Aryanized
like all the others.


454
00:26:29.066 --> 00:26:31.168
Surely you're aware
of that already.


455
00:26:31.769 --> 00:26:34.939
Maybe you should
just sign the order.


456
00:26:35.474 --> 00:26:36.907
We spared your boys.

457
00:26:37.508 --> 00:26:38.743
Be grateful.

458
00:26:39.944 --> 00:26:41.612
Who gave the order?

459
00:26:42.813 --> 00:26:45.484
We are to round up

460
00:26:45.616 --> 00:26:47.151
for work detail

461
00:26:47.284 --> 00:26:50.755
in the fields tomorrow
to clean up the countryside.


462
00:26:52.823 --> 00:26:54.426
Clean the countryside.

463
00:26:54.558 --> 00:26:55.993
Mr. Lowy...

464
00:26:56.527 --> 00:26:57.928
it's very important

465
00:26:58.062 --> 00:27:00.931
that people
will understand the new reality.


466
00:27:01.532 --> 00:27:02.967
To know their place.

467
00:27:03.100 --> 00:27:05.269
Jewish picking up rubbish...

468
00:27:05.836 --> 00:27:07.338
has a nice ring to it.

469
00:27:07.472 --> 00:27:09.140
[shouting] Who gave the order?

470
00:27:09.273 --> 00:27:12.043
Who gave this order?
Who gave it?


471
00:27:13.611 --> 00:27:15.913
-Let go!
-[indistinct].


472
00:27:16.847 --> 00:27:18.115
<i>Herr</i> Lowy.

473
00:27:19.316 --> 00:27:22.319
Jewish running
the show in Bardejov


474
00:27:22.454 --> 00:27:23.988
is a thing of the past.

475
00:27:24.755 --> 00:27:26.190
And if you would like

476
00:27:26.323 --> 00:27:28.692
to see the inside
of the jail again,


477
00:27:28.826 --> 00:27:31.228
I can happily arrange it.

478
00:27:35.366 --> 00:27:37.034
Get him away from me.

479
00:27:38.369 --> 00:27:40.371
[speaking other language]

480
00:27:40.505 --> 00:27:42.740
[clamoring]

481
00:27:45.576 --> 00:27:47.178
To [indistinct]. Quick!

482
00:27:47.311 --> 00:27:50.815
Lowy, use this.
As much as you need.


483
00:27:53.584 --> 00:27:56.821
Tell my wife I'm safe.
I'll be back in the morning.


484
00:27:58.823 --> 00:28:00.958
-Go!
-Good luck.


485
00:28:03.627 --> 00:28:05.564
[guards shouting]

486
00:28:05.696 --> 00:28:07.932
[tense music playing]

487
00:28:17.341 --> 00:28:19.376
[guards chanting]

488
00:28:26.784 --> 00:28:29.019
[guards cheering]

489
00:28:29.753 --> 00:28:31.789
Gabriel, hey, come here.
Come here.


490
00:28:31.922 --> 00:28:34.526
-[all] Come on. Come on.
-[Helena] Psst! Gabriel.


491
00:28:35.025 --> 00:28:37.328
Gabriel, hey, come here.

492
00:28:37.462 --> 00:28:38.497
Come on. Come on.

493
00:28:38.629 --> 00:28:40.831
Come here, yes.

494
00:28:43.267 --> 00:28:44.902
Yes.

495
00:28:46.036 --> 00:28:48.607
[guards shouting]

496
00:28:48.739 --> 00:28:50.875
Come on. Come on. Come on.

497
00:28:52.910 --> 00:28:55.679
[guards singing]

498
00:28:57.381 --> 00:29:00.217
[car honking]

499
00:29:10.861 --> 00:29:14.265
Don't follow me.
I'm not here for you, Mr. Lowy.


500
00:29:14.665 --> 00:29:16.568
I have business
with Captain Reisteiter.


501
00:29:16.700 --> 00:29:19.837
If this keeps, I can no longer
promise calm and cooperation.


502
00:29:19.970 --> 00:29:21.772
Our debts are clear now.

503
00:29:22.173 --> 00:29:25.843
Do your job Mr. Lowy
and stay clear.


504
00:29:37.087 --> 00:29:39.757
-Stefan!
-[objects clattering]


505
00:29:59.578 --> 00:30:01.011
It's not about the Jew.

506
00:30:01.680 --> 00:30:03.448
-Yes, it is.
-No.


507
00:30:05.015 --> 00:30:06.850
Let him think he was a big hero.

508
00:30:07.552 --> 00:30:09.787
I was going to have
a problem here regardless.


509
