00:44:38.189 --> 00:44:39.256
And then what?

769
00:44:39.757 --> 00:44:42.693
If they don't find her,
they'll come for you.


770
00:44:48.799 --> 00:44:50.801
Mama, they're going to go.

771
00:44:51.335 --> 00:44:52.636
It will be okay.

772
00:44:55.739 --> 00:44:58.008
-Magda.
-Mama, please.


773
00:44:58.776 --> 00:44:59.844
We're strong.

774
00:45:00.244 --> 00:45:02.213
We can work hard
and bring you money.


775
00:45:02.947 --> 00:45:05.116
I can't let you go, Helena.

776
00:45:05.683 --> 00:45:06.951
[Helena] Mama.

777
00:45:07.452 --> 00:45:08.520
Yes, you can.

778
00:45:08.919 --> 00:45:10.654
The other girls needs us, too.

779
00:45:11.423 --> 00:45:12.690
Don't worry.

780
00:45:16.160 --> 00:45:19.163
If you tell us to go, we will.

781
00:45:29.073 --> 00:45:30.975
Tell your friends to pack.

782
00:45:31.375 --> 00:45:32.643
Calmly.

783
00:45:35.112 --> 00:45:39.183
We will do everything we can
to get to the bottom of this.


784
00:45:41.118 --> 00:45:42.621
Now,

785
00:45:42.753 --> 00:45:44.121
everybody home.

786
00:45:44.688 --> 00:45:45.990
Get ready.

787
00:45:46.123 --> 00:45:48.692
Men, we going to meet
at the shul...


788
00:45:49.760 --> 00:45:52.497
the minute Refuel is back

789
00:45:52.631 --> 00:45:55.900
and we have only until two

790
00:45:56.033 --> 00:45:58.436
to get everything
we need for the girls


791
00:45:58.570 --> 00:46:00.070
then lock down.

792
00:46:05.676 --> 00:46:08.812
[somber music playing]

793
00:46:36.675 --> 00:46:38.409
[cupboard door creaking]

794
00:46:49.954 --> 00:46:52.256
[birds chirping]

795
00:47:04.268 --> 00:47:08.339
15 kilos,
one bag, clearly labeled.


796
00:47:08.707 --> 00:47:10.475
Wait for your escort.

797
00:47:12.176 --> 00:47:15.846
-Schondorf?
-32 Sokovia Street.


798
00:47:17.381 --> 00:47:19.883
[music continues]

799
00:47:25.055 --> 00:47:26.524
[banging on door]

800
00:47:43.407 --> 00:47:44.808
Helena Schondorf?

801
00:47:45.276 --> 00:47:46.310
Yes.

802
00:47:52.651 --> 00:47:55.420
[both breathing heavily]

803
00:48:04.895 --> 00:48:06.230
Don't worry.

804
00:48:06.830 --> 00:48:08.466
It's only for a few months.

805
00:48:09.434 --> 00:48:10.502
All right.

806
00:48:12.369 --> 00:48:18.942
â™ª

807
00:48:20.512 --> 00:48:22.980
[gate creaks closed]

808
00:48:34.492 --> 00:48:35.593
[goat bleating]

809
00:49:23.974 --> 00:49:26.478
All the Jews girls
ready for work.


810
00:49:39.089 --> 00:49:40.458
There.

811
00:49:50.033 --> 00:49:52.470
[engine humming]

812
00:50:14.759 --> 00:50:16.960
[doorbell dinging]

813
00:50:22.801 --> 00:50:24.301
I-- uh,

814
00:50:24.436 --> 00:50:26.671
I'm picking up a prescription

815
00:50:26.805 --> 00:50:28.138
for Hershe.

816
00:50:39.016 --> 00:50:40.552
I told you he'd show up.

817
00:50:40.984 --> 00:50:42.286
Glad you were expecting me.

818
00:50:42.420 --> 00:50:44.656
That means
you know what's going on.


819
00:50:44.955 --> 00:50:46.658
Tell me what you know.

820
00:50:46.791 --> 00:50:49.960
We know the Hlinka Guard, uh,
are involved in the roundups.


821
00:50:50.929 --> 00:50:53.565
Poprad is a local
transit center.


822
00:50:53.698 --> 00:50:55.700
At least 1000 people...

823
00:50:56.901 --> 00:50:59.036
girls in the next two days.

824
00:50:59.771 --> 00:51:03.641
Is there a--
a shoe factory in Brezovec?


825
00:51:07.411 --> 00:51:10.280
There is no
shoe factory in Brezovec.


826
00:51:14.184 --> 00:51:15.986
Where are the trains going?

827
00:51:19.791 --> 00:51:22.259
Where are the trains going?

828
00:51:22.392 --> 00:51:24.696
[tense music playing]

829
00:51:29.801 --> 00:51:33.905
[indistinct mumbling]

830
00:51:34.037 --> 00:51:35.038
Stop the car.

831
00:51:35.172 --> 00:51:37.174
[panting] Stop the car!

832
00:51:38.108 --> 00:51:41.044
[indistinct]

833
00:51:42.279 --> 00:51:46.451
[indistinct]

834
00:51:48.820 --> 00:51:50.722
[car honking]

835
00:51:50.855 --> 00:51:53.223
[engines revving]

836
00:51:54.157 --> 00:51:55.493
[brake squealing]

837
00:52:03.133 --> 00:52:04.334
What?

838
00:52:04.469 --> 00:52:05.837
What do you want, you d--

839
00:52:05.970 --> 00:52:07.170
[thudding]

840
00:52:07.304 --> 00:52:09.807
-[both yelling]
-You dog! You dog!


841
00:52:09.941 --> 00:52:12.510
-You dog.
-[both grunting]


842
00:52:13.745 --> 00:52:16.014
Stop, stop, stop, stop.
Stop. Stop.


843
00:52:16.146 --> 00:52:17.482
[indistinct]

844
00:52:18.816 --> 00:52:20.618
[groaning]

845
00:52:20.752 --> 00:52:21.819
[gun clicking]

846
00:52:24.388 --> 00:52:26.056
We shall see, Jew.

847
00:52:26.189 --> 00:52:28.526
[Lowy laughing maniacally]

848
00:52:31.930 --> 00:52:34.164
[breathing heavily]

849
00:52:45.108 --> 00:52:48.111
Let's go. [laughing]

850
00:52:50.648 --> 00:52:52.417
[speaking in other language]

851
00:52:54.986 --> 00:52:56.821
[car engine starts]

852
00:53:02.192 --> 00:53:04.862
[tense music playing]

853
00:53:10.034 --> 00:53:11.301
Lowy.

854
00:53:12.369 --> 00:53:13.403
Tell us they're okay.

855
00:53:13.538 --> 00:53:14.806
You found the factory?

856
00:53:17.809 --> 00:53:18.977
Auschwitz.

857
00:53:19.444 --> 00:53:21.278
-Auschwitz?
-[Rabbi] Auschwitz?


858
00:53:21.411 --> 00:53:23.313
-[Mayer] Auschwitz?
-Auschwitz?


859
00:53:23.448 --> 00:53:26.417
A camp called Auschwitz.
Prisoner camp.


860
00:53:29.454 --> 00:53:31.589
The prisoners
are making shoes now?


861
00:53:33.323 --> 00:53:34.592
[Lowy chuckles]

862
00:53:35.927 --> 00:53:37.729
It's not a shoe factory.

863
00:53:38.963 --> 00:53:40.431
[Erwin] What is it then?

864
00:53:43.868 --> 00:53:46.037
Executions. Gassings.

865
00:53:46.471 --> 00:53:48.238
-[Erwin sighs]
-It's a death camp.


866
00:53:54.378 --> 00:53:55.880
They have already killed...

867
00:53:56.848 --> 00:53:57.982
hundreds of Russians.

868
00:53:58.416 --> 00:54:01.284
-Jews?
-No, not yet.


869
00:54:02.954 --> 00:54:05.188
But they're building a new camp.

870
00:54:05.322 --> 00:54:07.224
A massive new camp...

871
00:54:07.959 --> 00:54:09.226
for us.

872
00:54:12.362 --> 00:54:14.899
Our girls are not
coming back from there.


873
00:54:15.033 --> 00:54:16.901
Not just our girls.

874
00:54:17.869 --> 00:54:18.936
Thousands...

875
00:54:21.171 --> 00:54:23.141
of Jewish girls
from all over Slovakia.


876
00:54:23.273 --> 00:54:25.677
[sighs] We cannot let them go.

877
00:54:26.811 --> 00:54:29.947
-Let's storm the school.
-Have you seen how many guards?


878
00:54:30.081 --> 00:54:33.551
-It's suicide if we do that.
-Let's call the partisans.


879
00:54:33.685 --> 00:54:34.886
My Helena.

880
00:54:38.255 --> 00:54:39.791
They are still right here.

881
00:54:39.924 --> 00:54:41.559
We have to do something.

882
00:54:42.560 --> 00:54:45.463
Lowy, what are you thinking?

883
00:54:46.597 --> 00:54:48.966
Soviet war, [indistinct],

884
00:54:49.100 --> 00:54:51.536
mass murder, gas chambers.

885
00:54:52.302 --> 00:54:54.337
All true.

886
00:54:54.472 --> 00:54:57.442
Now Auschwitz, now our girls...

887
00:54:58.341 --> 00:55:00.210
and we're going to be next.

888
00:55:00.343 --> 00:55:02.279
We'll follow them
to the slaughter.


889
00:55:03.147 --> 00:55:04.415
Faster! Go!

890
00:55:04.549 --> 00:55:06.050
[Lowy]
The fate of Slovakian Jewry


891
00:55:06.184 --> 00:55:07.785
is written on the wall.

892
00:55:08.453 --> 00:55:09.554
[all crying]

893
00:55:09.687 --> 00:55:11.756
But wishing it was different...

894
00:55:11.889 --> 00:55:13.223
Sit down. Fast!

895
00:55:13.356 --> 00:55:14.425
[Lowy] ...won't change.

896
00:55:15.193 --> 00:55:19.396
Thousands of girls were stolen
from their homes tonight.


897
00:55:20.397 --> 00:55:22.166
And how many more to follow?

898
00:55:22.834 --> 00:55:25.670
We need to send
the world a message.


899
00:55:27.972 --> 00:55:29.674
What you're suggesting?

900
00:55:30.775 --> 00:55:34.746
I have enough gasoline
and gunpowder in my warehouse...


901
00:55:35.613 --> 00:55:37.982
to blow the whole
of Bardejov sky high...


902
00:55:39.417 --> 00:55:41.686
Bardejov burn to the ground

903
00:55:41.819 --> 00:55:43.855
by its people, by the Jews.

904
00:55:44.254 --> 00:55:46.424
And the Germans
will then understand


905
00:55:46.557 --> 00:55:48.760
that they cannot
take us and leave.


906
00:55:50.161 --> 00:55:52.329
Many people will die.

907
00:55:53.396 --> 00:55:55.032
Many Jews will die.

908
00:55:55.433 --> 00:55:56.768
I know.

909
00:55:57.135 --> 00:55:59.470
They take our daughters...

910
00:56:00.370 --> 00:56:02.405
and-- and we kill theirs?

911
00:56:02.540 --> 00:56:05.076
We save our daughters
and who knows how many.


912
00:56:06.244 --> 00:56:09.614
There will be no train
leaving from Bardejov tomorrow.


913
00:56:10.548 --> 00:56:12.717
There will be no Bardejov.

914
00:56:13.417 --> 00:56:14.752
Where we will go?

915
00:56:15.352 --> 00:56:17.088
We'll all be shot within hours.

916
00:56:17.221 --> 00:56:18.956
Killed like animals.

917
00:56:19.090 --> 00:56:20.191
By-- by whom?

918
00:56:20.625 --> 00:56:23.360
They will be running
for their lives, too.


919
00:56:25.563 --> 00:56:26.831
Uh, Lowy...

920
00:56:27.999 --> 00:56:29.600
I cannot allow it.

921
00:56:30.735 --> 00:56:33.538
The only question is, what...

922
00:56:34.472 --> 00:56:36.440
does God say?

923
00:56:37.642 --> 00:56:41.612
In here,
I don't think He says yes.


924
00:56:47.752 --> 00:56:50.488
[Lowy] Here.
Come here. [indistinct]


925
00:56:55.126 --> 00:56:56.494
[Adam exhales sharply]

926
00:56:56.627 --> 00:57:00.164
Good evening,
Mr. Bear and Mr. Rabbit.


927
00:57:00.731 --> 00:57:02.900
[laughs]
You have a carrot for me?


928
00:57:03.034 --> 00:57:06.504
[laughs] I'm just joking.
Give me a cigarette.


929
00:57:06.637 --> 00:57:09.406
-I'm scared.
-Be brave.


930
00:57:11.876 --> 00:57:14.045
Listen, guys,
I have something for you.


931
00:57:15.847 --> 00:57:16.981
Pure gold.

932
00:57:17.615 --> 00:57:19.951
Follow me. Follow me.

933
00:57:23.087 --> 00:57:25.489
You could buy
something for your wife,


934
00:57:25.623 --> 00:57:28.092
your second wife. [laughs]

935
00:57:30.528 --> 00:57:32.096
Here, take the watch.

936
00:57:32.697 --> 00:57:36.500
And for you, Mr. Rabbit,
you can take it all.


937
00:57:37.168 --> 00:57:38.401
That's for you.

938
00:57:41.072 --> 00:57:44.308
Ah, you saw
the football game yesterday.


939
00:57:44.442 --> 00:57:46.409
[laughs] They got them Germans.

940
00:57:46.544 --> 00:57:48.378
They know how to play.
Huh? [chuckles]


941
00:57:48.512 --> 00:57:49.747
[breathing heavily]

942
00:57:49.881 --> 00:57:51.482
It's all right. 
It's all right.

943
00:57:51.616 --> 00:57:53.050
It's going to be okay.

944
00:57:53.751 --> 00:57:55.887
It's okay. It's okay.

945
00:57:56.020 --> 00:57:57.121
Here.

946
00:57:58.356 --> 00:57:59.557
She must come with me!

947
00:57:59.690 --> 00:58:01.359
It's all right.
What's the matter?


948
00:58:01.492 --> 00:58:03.594
She's sick. She must be removed.

949
00:58:03.728 --> 00:58:05.263
She's just scared.
Leave her alone.


950
00:58:05.395 --> 00:58:07.999
-It's all right.
-[panting] Mommy.


951
00:58:08.132 --> 00:58:09.467
She has typhus.

952
00:58:09.600 --> 00:58:11.702
-She cannot stay.
-She's just scared.


953
00:58:12.370 --> 00:58:14.272
Leave us. I'll bring her to you.

954
00:58:14.404 --> 00:58:16.406
[breathing heavily]

955
00:58:17.608 --> 00:58:19.610
-[whimpering]
-Everything will be okay.


956
00:58:19.744 --> 00:58:21.312
At least she will go home.

957
00:58:21.812 --> 00:58:24.015
[tense music playing]

958
00:58:26.317 --> 00:58:27.752
Okay. I'm sorry.

959
00:58:27.885 --> 00:58:29.787
Thank you. God bless you.

960
00:58:34.592 --> 00:58:36.527
-[Giselle] Shh.
-[breathing heavily]


961
00:58:37.995 --> 00:58:40.131
[indistinct]

962
00:58:41.065 --> 00:58:42.934
-Give it to me.
-Thank you.


963
00:58:44.001 --> 00:58:46.137
Take that to him. 
Do it quickly.

964
00:58:46.737 --> 00:58:49.740
[whimpering]

965
00:58:53.144 --> 00:58:55.079
Adam. Adam.

966
00:58:59.383 --> 00:59:01.285
-Take this.
-What is it?


967
00:59:01.886 --> 00:59:03.154
Just-- just take it.

968
00:59:04.088 --> 00:59:05.189
Thank you.

969
00:59:28.012 --> 00:59:29.080
[Lowy] Come.

970
00:59:29.914 --> 00:59:32.417
There's no way out.
It's sealed shut.


971
00:59:32.550 --> 00:59:34.752
Barbed wire, barricades.

972
00:59:34.885 --> 00:59:36.587
They're [indistinct]
the extra troops.


973
00:59:36.721 --> 00:59:39.390
You will never be able
to take 300 girls.


974
00:59:40.291 --> 00:59:43.127
If you have someone here
that know how to speak with God,


975
00:59:43.260 --> 00:59:44.729
now it's the time.

976
00:59:47.365 --> 00:59:48.632
From the girls.

977
00:59:55.573 --> 00:59:58.242
[tense music playing]

978
01:00:01.212 --> 01:00:02.813
Is there a way in?

979
01:00:03.381 --> 01:00:04.682
I don't know. I...

980
01:00:06.217 --> 01:00:07.718
I suppose.

981
01:00:10.054 --> 01:00:11.922
[Erwin] What are you
going to do, Mr. Lowy?


982
01:00:12.056 --> 01:00:15.292
-Blow it up?
-[Lowy laughs]


983
01:00:20.898 --> 01:00:22.434
Besides the Jews...

984
01:00:23.468 --> 01:00:26.404
what is the one thing
the Germans are most afraid of?


985
01:00:26.537 --> 01:00:28.139
There are no Germans here, Lowy.

986
01:00:28.272 --> 01:00:30.174
Yes, yes there are.

987
01:00:31.575 --> 01:00:33.377
Auschwitz is theirs.

988
01:00:33.512 --> 01:00:34.979
This is their plan.

989
01:00:35.713 --> 01:00:37.548
Hlinka Guards
are their errand boys.


990
01:00:37.681 --> 01:00:38.983
They're here.

991
01:00:39.984 --> 01:00:41.919
And what are
they most afraid of?


992
01:00:42.053 --> 01:00:44.423
-The Russians?
-No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.


993
01:00:44.889 --> 01:00:46.991
What kills their plans?

994
01:00:47.124 --> 01:00:48.759
Puts a wrench
in their whole machine?


995
01:00:48.893 --> 01:00:50.795
-Kills production?
-Enough!


996
01:00:51.228 --> 01:00:52.329
What?

997
01:00:53.498 --> 01:00:54.965
Typhus.

998
01:00:57.601 --> 01:00:59.637
-It's brilliant.
-[Lowy laughs]


999
01:00:59.770 --> 01:01:02.773
If we can get
enough serum for the girls,


1000
01:01:02.907 --> 01:01:04.275
if we can get in...

1001
01:01:05.109 --> 01:01:08.779
it'll create an epidemic.

1002
01:01:09.980 --> 01:01:11.382
How much do we need?

1003
01:01:11.516 --> 01:01:14.919
A double dose of serum
will bring out symptoms.


1004
01:01:15.052 --> 01:01:16.521
That should be enough.

1005
01:01:16.654 --> 01:01:19.156
It will declare
Bardejov of infected.


1006
01:01:19.290 --> 01:01:21.560
Seal us off
and force a quarantine.


1007
01:01:21.692 --> 01:01:22.927
Who has the authority?

1008
01:01:23.060 --> 01:01:25.796
Dr. Milos Baratis
in [indistinct]


1009
01:01:25.930 --> 01:01:28.365
is a district head medic.

1010
01:01:28.500 --> 01:01:30.868
So how many people
need to show symptoms?


1011
01:01:31.001 --> 01:01:32.903
Five won't stop the trains.

1012
01:01:34.238 --> 01:01:35.372
10-15...

1013
01:01:36.240 --> 01:01:37.274
should do it.

1014
01:01:37.408 --> 01:01:39.643
How dangerous is a double dose?

1015
01:01:44.982 --> 01:01:47.251
-There is a risk.
-A real risk.


1016
01:01:48.085 --> 01:01:50.721
An outbreak, maybe worse.

1017
01:01:51.590 --> 01:01:53.324
But there are guards everywhere.

1018
01:01:53.458 --> 01:01:55.626
How will we even get inside?

1019
01:01:55.759 --> 01:01:57.895
-Boris.
-The plumber?


1020
01:01:58.829 --> 01:02:00.664
He has access to the sewers.

1021
01:02:01.132 --> 01:02:02.766
They run directly
beneath the school.


1022
01:02:02.900 --> 01:02:04.335
Forget about how we get in.

1023
01:02:04.469 --> 01:02:07.104
H-- how can we get
enough serum this quickly?


1024
01:02:07.238 --> 01:02:08.305
Kosice.

1025
01:02:09.541 --> 01:02:10.609
In Kosice.

1026
01:02:10.741 --> 01:02:12.710
It's a two hour drive.

1027
01:02:13.344 --> 01:02:16.814
And they're not exactly
waiting for us either.


1028
01:02:16.947 --> 01:02:18.782
You-- you won't be back
till midnight.


1029
01:02:18.916 --> 01:02:21.018
Who says it's enough time

1030
01:02:21.152 --> 01:02:23.287
for the serum to take effect?

1031
